sequenceDiagram
    participant User1 as User 1<br/>(Alice)
    participant UI1 as UI1<br/>Dashboard
    participant StatusCtrl as Status Controller
    participant StatusSvc as Status Service
    participant StatusRepo as Status Repository
    participant Cache as Redis Cache
    participant WS as WebSocket/STOMP<br/>Broker
    participant UI2 as UI2<br/>Team Dashboard
    participant User2 as User 2<br/>(Bob - watching team)
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    
    User1->>UI1: Set status to "IN_OFFICE"
    UI1->>StatusCtrl: POST /api/status/me<br/>{status: "IN_OFFICE"}
    
    StatusCtrl->>StatusSvc: setStatus(userId, request)
    
    StatusSvc->>StatusRepo: Save/Update status
    StatusRepo->>DB: INSERT/UPDATE user_statuses
    DB->>StatusRepo: Success
    
    StatusSvc->>Cache: Invalidate cache<br/>teamDashboard_*
    
    StatusSvc->>WS: Publish to /topic/status<br/>StatusUpdatedEvent
    
    WS->>UI1: Confirm update received
    UI1->>User1: Show "Status Updated"
    
    WS->>UI2: Broadcast status change<br/>for Alice
    
    UI2->>User2: Update live dashboard<br/>Alice is now IN_OFFICE
    
    Note over StatusSvc,DB: Future: Event published to Kafka<br/>for analytics & audit trail
